article.headline: Phoenix win 16th straight game
article.linkText: Wis.-Green Bay clinches share of league title
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Tiffany Mor scored 23 points and Nicole Soulis added 18 as No. 23 Wisconsin-Green Bay beat Cleveland State 78-61 on Thursday night to clinch at least a share of the Horizon League title.

Green Bay has won or shared the league's regular-season championship in each of head coach Kevin Borseth's seven seasons. The Phoenix can take the league title outright with a victory Saturday against Youngstown State.

Green Bay won its 16th straight game and improved to 22-2 overall, the best start in the program's 32-year history. The Phoenix also won their 55th consecutive home game against a conference opponent and are 13-0 in league play.

Mor and Soulis, both post players, shot a combined 19-of-26 from the field. Abby Scharlow barely missed a triple-double for Green Bay, finishing with 12 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds.

Erin Martin led Cleveland State (3-21, 2-11) with 19 points, and Omega Harrington added 16.

Green Bay shot 65 percent from the field and scored a season-high 46 points in the first 20 minutes. Soulis had seven points during a 14-2 run that put the Phoenix ahead 38-20, and the lead grew as high as 28 midway through the second half.
